# Log4shell

# Usage

snyk log4shell

# Description

The snyk log4shell command finds traces of the Log4J library that are affected by the Log4Shell vulnerability CVE-2021-44228open in new window, even if this library is not declared in the manifest files (such as pom.xml or build.gradle).

# Managed projects

To test for Log4Shell vulnerabilities in Java projects using their package manager manifest files, use the snyk test command. See the test command helpopen in new window and Snyk for Java and Kotlinopen in new window.

To test unmanaged files, use snyk test --scan-all-unmanaged. See the Maven options section of the test command helpopen in new window.

# Exit codes

Possible exit codes and their meaning:

0: success, Log4Shell not found
1: action_needed, Log4Shell found
2: failure, try to re-run command

# Debug

Use the -d option to output the debug logs.
